JSON : 

JSON means Javascript Object Notation
Strore and transport data between client and server.

client (browser JS) --- > JSON.stringify() --- > JSON 
JSON   ----->   JSON.parse() ---->  client(browser JS)

JSON is simple
JSON is human and machine readable 
JSON is lightweight
JSON is langauge independent 
JSON is universal format.
we can store and transport data bw client and server 

 JSON available in two different formats.

 1. Array   (JSONArray) [ ]
 2. Object  (JSONObject) { }

 if we want to convert javascript to json   we need to use JSON.Stringify() method 

 if we want to convert JSON to javascript we need to use JSON.parse() method

JSON Object : { }

 { "name" : "srinivas",
     "age" : 32,
      "Qual" :"MCA",
      "Graduated": true
  }

rules of JSON Object:
  1. Object starts with { close with }
  2. key must be a string 
  3. value can be any datatype 
   (int,float,char,bool,string,null)
  4. key and value separated with colon.
  5. every key-value pair separated with comma 
  6. last key-value pair doesnot have comma

  Note : JSON file saved as .json format  

rules of JSON Array :
1. JSON Array starts with [ ends with ]
2. JSON Array is a collection of  values 
3. value can be any datatype
4. values are separated with comma 
5. last value doenot have comma 

JSON validation:

    https://jsoncompare.com/#!/simple/

    copy and paste json here  and click on lint button 
     if any error came it will not compile 
     if JSON is right json it will do validate 























